The paper discusses a software system for handling neural networks as filters of stream pipelines, which is relevant to computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The focus on on-device AI and the need for efficient development and execution of neural network applications also suggests the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The use of off-shelf multimedia stream filters and the applicability to a wide range of hardware architectures and software platforms indicates the multimedia (cs.MM) and systems and control (cs.SY) sub-categories may also be relevant.
